<div>
	<p style="margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;padding:0;">
		 </p>
	<p style="margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;padding:0;">
		<span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">Booth attendance was high, with consistent traffic throughout the entire show. We were particularly excited about the strong turnout for BEACON AMA product demonstrations, with a number of customers visiting solely for that reason.</span></p>
	<p style="margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;padding:0;">
		 </p>
	<p style="margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;padding:0;">
		<span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">Other highlights included:</span></p>
	<ul><li>
			<span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">ACE14 Technical Session, "How Is Technology Changing the Water Utility Industry?", hosted by Badger Meter</span>.</li>
		<li>
			<span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;"><a href="http://youtu.be/hwdRW2EuLUY" style="color:#0000FF!important;">Water Online radio interview</a> with John Fillinger. </span>
</li>
		<li>
			<span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">Video interview with Kristie Anderson and AWWA (link to video coming soon)</span>.</li>
		<li>
			<span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">CEO Reception at the Boston Tea Party Museum, hosted by Rich Meeusen.</span>
</li>
		<li>
			<span style="font-family:verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">New England Microbrews and Martinis at the Badger Meter booth (featuring the "Flowing B Stinger")!</span>
</li>
	</ul><p style="margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;padding:0;">
